'''马蹄瀑布'''（{{lang-en|Horseshoe Falls}}，也称作'''加拿大瀑布''')，是北美洲[[尼亚加拉瀑布|尼亚加拉瀑布]]的一部分，属于[[尼亚加拉河|尼亚加拉河]]。该瀑布横跨[[美国|美国]]和[[加拿大|加拿大]]两国，马蹄瀑布的约2/3的位于加拿大的[[安大略省|安大略省]]，剩余的1/3位于美国的[[纽约州|纽约州]]西南部接壤地带。<ref name="regina2006">Staff report (June 23, 2006). [http://www.canada.com/reginaleaderpost/news/story.html?id=2c398fd4-3a94-46e8-8228-305b1a3d502b Campaign blunder puts Yankee spin on Canada's national anthem.] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110628223428/http://www.canada.com/reginaleaderpost/news/story.html?id=2c398fd4-3a94-46e8-8228-305b1a3d502b |date=2011-06-28 }} ''[[Regina_Leader-Post|Regina Leader-Post]]''</ref><ref name="Lee2007">Lee, Matthew (October 29, 2007). [http://www.thestar.com/News/article/271424 Video claims Horseshoe Falls for U.S.] ''[[Toronto_Star|Toronto Star]]''</ref><ref name="1911hearings">"The international boundary line may pass through the Horseshoe Falls just beyond Terrapin Tower Point, so that the United States are not entitled to as large a portion as Canada of the Horseshoe Falls, which is admittedly not all Canadian." Statement of Mr. J Boardman Scovell. ''Preservation of Niagara Falls: hearings on the subject of H.R. 26688, Sixty-first Congress, second session, relating to the control and regulation of the waters of Niagara River and the preservation of Niagara Falls, held before the Committee on Rivers and Harbors of the House of Representatives.'' U.S. G.P.O., 1911</ref>

